headline: Campbell's (CPB): Buy, Sell, or Hold Post Q2 Earnings?
summary: Over the past six months, Campbell’s stock price fell to $31.28. Shareholders have lost 11.9% of their capital, which is disappointing considering the S&P 500 has climbed by 13%. This may have investors wondering how to approach the situation.
